All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Application  
    CSVParser
    This class is used to read a CSV file and fill a Pharmacy and a Metadata vectors.
    FileManager
    Used by both application and CSVParser.
    FilterParameters
    Contains the parameters from the body of the POST requests used by the filters.
    JSONParser
    Has as attributes a file name and a url and it is used to parse the initial url in order to find another url that downloads the CSV file.
    Metadata
    Used by CSVParser to store the first line with the fields of the data-set.
    NumberStats
    Statistics returned by "/stats/{fieldName}" and "/filter/stats/{fieldName}".
    Pharmacy
    Represents a generic pharmacy that can describe the rows of the dataset.
    PharmacyController
    Manages the Spring application and define the filters using GET or POST requests.
    PharmacyService
    Contains the methods used by the controller or the service itself to manage the filters.
